\title{Derivation}
\taxon{Term}

\p{A derivation is a sequence of applications of rules in some type theory, starting from the empty premise and concluding in a judgment.}

\p{See [Rule of inference](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rule_of_inference) on wikipedia for an introduction to this sort of thing. The only difference is that a derivation in type theory typically expresses that there is a term of a certain type rather than just expressing that a proposition is true.}

\p{A principled approach to derivations may be found in [[shulman-2016-categorical]].}
